<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#ffb3b3" WIDTH="150"><B>Conclusion</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">It seems to me apparent that the taxing<BR ALIGN='left'/>question of this transaction was<BR ALIGN='left'/>correctly handled in the first instance,<BR ALIGN='left'/>and should not now be disturbed. In<BR ALIGN='left'/>reaching this conclusion, I wish to<BR ALIGN='left'/>state plainly that I do not think<BR ALIGN='left'/>plaintiff by its actions thus far is now<BR ALIGN='left'/>estopped to press its present<BR ALIGN='left'/>contention; but the facts to my mind are<BR ALIGN='left'/>very apparent that the transaction of<BR ALIGN='left'/>January 1, 1939, was a reorganization or<BR ALIGN='left'/>merger, pursuant to a plan of<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganization, and in no sense of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>word a sale or exchange.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
